{"questionId":"26941","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the curve&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mi>x</mi></msqrt></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Hence show that the equation of the tangent to the curve at the point&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>16</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>gradient at&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>16</mn></math>&nbsp;is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>16</mn></msqrt></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn></math></p>\n<p><br><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>16</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>16</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Do not allow working backwards from the given answer.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p>hence&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"26941","referenceCode":"22M.2.AHL.TZ1.6a.ii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Hence show that the equation of the tangent to the curve at the point 0.16, 0.4 is y=1.25x+0.2.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.4—Tangents and normal"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}